cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition in depth videos using multimodal features. The use of joint sparse regression and hierarchical mixed norm also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of depth and skeleton-based features could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper's focus on modeling actions as a combination of features suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of structured sparsity and group feature selection could also suggest that it belongs to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
